+# CZSServiceList
+
+This repository contains a Node.js backend and React frontend.
+
+## Environment Variables
+
+Backend configuration relies on environment variables. Copy `backend/.env.example` to `backend/.env` and adjust values as needed:
+
+```
+cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
+```
+
+Variables include MySQL and MSSQL credentials as well as optional B2B API credentials. `DB_DRIVER` controls whether the backend uses MySQL (default) or a SQLite database.
+
+## SQLite Test Database
+
+For development or testing without access to MySQL, set `DB_DRIVER=sqlite` in `backend/.env` and run:
+
+```
+node backend/scripts/init_sqlite.js
+```
+
+This creates `backend/test.db` with sample data.
+
